full_threads.body:
Hi Chris,

Thanks for getting back to me.

After doing a little bit of research, looks like Elementor does not work directly with ACF repeater fields. I'm not 100% sure if this is the case. If purchasing a 3rd party plugin (Anywhere Elementor, etc) will be easier, then happy to go in this direction.

Initially, I thought of switching to jet engine so it's similar to the MS Australia main website but was worried that I would need to restructure the content/fields of existing clinical trials and retrain the research staff assigned to this on how to update posts. I'm undecided if I should be doing this now while we only have 55 posts, or just revisit this in a year or so.

Would like to hear your thoughts/recommendations.

Thanks
Karlo

Hi Karlo,

It's no trouble at all. The only thing to remember is that when a staging server is used all updates on the live domain need to be paused.

A staging server provides you with significantly more freedom to test without affecting the live domain.

Also great to read about moving from WP Bakery to Elementor!

Please let me know if you'd like to set up the staging server and I will loop back with access.

Regards,
